(86, 5, 3, 'Retail inflation shows signs of moderation', '<h2>üìâ Inflation Eases: Retail Prices Show Moderation</h2><p><strong>Latest economic data</strong> indicates that retail inflation has <em>begun moderating</em> after several months of <u>elevated levels</u>.</p><h3>Inflation Trends:</h3><h4>Current Numbers:</h4><ul><li>üíµ <strong>CPI Inflation:</strong> 5.8% (down from 6.3%)</li><li><strong>Food Inflation:</strong> 4.9% (previous 6.1%)</li><li><strong>Core Inflation:</strong> 5.5% (relatively stable)</li><li><strong>Trend:</strong> Downward trajectory observed</li></ul><h4>Price Stabilization:</h4><p><strong>Food prices</strong>, which constitute a significant portion of CPI, have stabilized:</p><ol><li><strong>Vegetables:</strong> Prices cooling after seasonal spike</li><li><strong>Pulses:</strong> Import measures easing costs</li><li><strong>Edible Oils:</strong> Global prices declining</li><li><strong>Cereals:</strong> Good harvest keeping prices stable</li></ol><h3>Contributing Factors:</h3><h4>Why Inflation is Moderating:</h4><ul><li>üõçÔ∏è <strong>Supply Chains:</strong> Improved logistics and distribution</li><li><strong>Agricultural Output:</strong> Good monsoon and favorable harvest</li><li><strong>Government Action:</strong> Strategic releases from buffer stocks</li><li><strong>Global Prices:</strong> Commodity price softening</li></ul><h4>Economist Views:</h4><p><em>Economic experts</em> are cautiously optimistic:</p><ul><li><strong>Positive Sign:</strong> Validates RBI\'s policy stance</li><li><strong>Interest Rates:</strong> May influence future monetary decisions</li><li><strong>Growth Support:</strong> Lower inflation boosts consumption</li><li><strong>Monitoring:</strong> Need to sustain the trend</li></ul><blockquote>\"The moderation in retail inflation is encouraging news. Stabilizing food prices particularly help lower-income households. The central bank will closely monitor this trend in making future interest rate decisions. Sustainable price stability is crucial for balanced economic growth,\" stated economists.</blockquote><p>A <strong>relief</strong> for consumers! üìà</p>', 'article-5-1619444837.jpeg', '2021-06-18', 0, 1),
(87, 6, 4, 'Young chess prodigy wins international championship', '<h2>‚ôüÔ∏è Chess Prodigy Makes History: Teenager Wins International Title!</h2><p>A <strong>teenage chess player</strong> has created history by winning a <em>prestigious international championship</em>, defeating several <u>grandmasters</u> along the way.</p><h3>Championship Victory:</h3><h4>Tournament Performance:</h4><ul><li>üèÜ <strong>Title Won:</strong> International Youth Championship</li><li><strong>Age:</strong> Just 16 years old</li><li><strong>Undefeated:</strong> 9 wins, 2 draws in 11 rounds</li><li><strong>Rating Gain:</strong> +85 ELO points</li><li><strong>GM Scalps:</strong> Defeated 3 grandmasters</li></ul><h4>Key Matches:</h4><p>The young champion displayed <em>exceptional skills</em> throughout:</p><ol><li><strong>Round 5:</strong> Brilliant queen sacrifice against GM opponent</li><li><strong>Round 8:</strong> Endgame masterclass in rook ending</li><li><strong>Round 10:</strong> Tactical brilliancy winning piece</li><li><strong>Final Round:</strong> Calm draw to secure title</li></ol><h3>Journey to Success:</h3><h4>Training and Development:</h4><ul><li>üß† <strong>Early Start:</strong> Began playing at age 5</li><li><strong>Structured Training:</strong> 6-8 hours daily practice</li><li><strong>Mental Conditioning:</strong> Sports psychology support</li><li><strong>International Exposure:</strong> 50+ tournaments worldwide</li><li><strong>Coach Support:</strong> Guidance from former national champion</li></ul><h4>Family Support:</h4><p>The player <strong>credited success</strong> to family backing:</p><ul><li><strong>Parents:</strong> Emotional and financial support</li><li><strong>Sacrifices:</strong> Family relocated for better training</li><li><strong>Encouragement:</strong> Never pressured, always supported</li></ul><h3>Impact on Indian Chess:</h3><blockquote>\"This achievement brings attention to India\'s growing strength in chess. After Viswanathan Anand, we\'re seeing a new