(106, 7, 4, 'Regional cinema gains recognition at national film awards', '<h2>üé¨ Regional Cinema Triumphs: National Awards Celebrate Diversity</h2><p><strong>Regional language films</strong> dominated the <em>national film awards</em> this year, with <u>multiple awards</u> for best film, direction, and performances.</p><h3>Award Winners:</h3><h4>Major Categories:</h4><ul><li>üèÜ <strong>Best Film:</strong> Malayalam drama on social issues</li><li><strong>Best Director:</strong> Tamil filmmaker for bold narrative</li><li><strong>Best Actor:</strong> Marathi actor for powerful role</li><li><strong>Best Actress:</strong> Bengali actress for nuanced performance</li><li><strong>Best Screenplay:</strong> Telugu writer for original story</li></ul><h4>Language Representation:</h4><p><em>Multiple languages</em> celebrated:</p><ol><li><strong>Malayalam:</strong> 8 awards (highest)</li><li><strong>Tamil:</strong> 6 awards</li><li><strong>Marathi:</strong> 5 awards</li><li><strong>Bengali:</strong> 4 awards</li><li><strong>Telugu:</strong> 3 awards</li><li><strong>Kannada:</strong> 2 awards</li></ol><h3>Cinematic Excellence:</h3><h4>Storytelling Traditions:</h4><ul><li>üåü <strong>Rich Narratives:</strong> Deep storytelling traditions</li><li><strong>Cultural Authenticity:</strong> Local stories, global appeal</li><li><strong>Technical Excellence:</strong> World-class production values</li><li><strong>Social Commentary:</strong> Films addressing real issues</li></ul><h4>Industry Evolution:</h4><p><strong>Regional cinema</strong> has transformed:</p><ul><li><strong>Production Quality:</strong> Matching international standards</li><li><strong>Distribution:</strong> Pan-India releases common</li><li><strong>Star Power:</strong> Regional stars gaining national fame</li><li><strong>Budget Growth:</strong> Bigger investments in content</li></ul><h3>Streaming Platform Impact:</h3><h4>Digital Revolution:</h4><p>Platforms <strong>boosting regional content</strong>:</p><ul><li><stron