(120, 6, 4, 'Table tennis academy produces international medalists', '<h2>üèì Ping Pong Power: Academy Creates Champions</h2><p>A <strong>specialized table tennis training academy</strong> has successfully developed <em>players who have won medals</em> at <u>international competitions</u>.</p><h3>Academy Success:</h3><h4>Medal Tally:</h4><ul><li>üèÜ <strong>International Medals:</strong> 15 medals in 3 years</li><li><strong>Commonwealth Games:</strong> 2 gold, 1 silver, 1 bronze</li><li><strong>Asian Championships:</strong> 3 silver, 2 bronze</li><li><strong>Youth Olympics:</strong> 1 gold, 2 silver</li><li><strong>World Rankings:</strong> 5 players in top 100</li></ul><h4>Star Players:</h4><p><em>Notable achievements</em>:</p><ol><li><strong>Manika Batra Academy Graduate:</strong> CWG champion</li><li><strong>Junior World Champion:</strong> 16-year-old prodigy</li><li><strong>Doubles Specialists:</strong> Ranked top 20 globally</li><li><strong>Para Athletes:</strong> Paralympic medalists trained</li></ol><h3>Training Methodology:</h3><h4>Systematic Approach:</h4><ul><li>üáÆüá≥ <strong>Technical Training:</strong> Stroke perfection (4 hours daily)</li><li><strong>Physical Fitness:</strong> Agility, reflexes, endurance</li><li><strong>Mental Conditioning:</strong> Sports psychology sessions</li><li><strong>Match Practice:</strong> Competitive exposure regularly</li></ul><h4>Training Schedule:</h4><p><strong>Rigorous daily routine</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>6:00 AM:</strong> Fitness training</li><li><strong>8:00 AM:</strong> Breakfast and rest</li><li><strong>10:00 AM:</strong> Technical drills</li><li><strong>1:00 PM:</strong> Lunch break</li><li><strong>3:00 PM:</strong> Match practice</li><li><strong>6:00 PM:</strong> Video analysis</li><li><strong>7:00 PM:</strong> Mental training</li></ul><h3>Competitive Exposure:</h3><h4>Tournament Participation:</h4><blockquote>\"Young players receive scholarships based on talent and potential. The academy\'s systematic approach combines technical training, mental conditioning, and competitive exposure. The success has attracted aspiring players from across the country to enroll in the program,\" stated the head coach.</blockquote><h4>International Experience:</h4><p><strong>Exposure opportunities</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Foreign Training:</strong> China, Germany camps</li><li><strong>International Leagues:</strong> European club participation</li><li><strong>World Tours:</strong> ITTF circuit events</li><li><strong>Sparring Partners:</strong> Training with top 10 players</li></ul><h3>Scholarship Program:</h3><h4>Talent Identification:</h4><p>Academy <strong>scouts nationwide</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>District Trials:</strong> Talent hunts in every state</li><li><strong>Selection Criteria:</strong> Potential over current skill</li><li><strong>Full Scholarship:</strong> 50 players annually</li><li><strong>Covering:</strong> Training, boarding, education, equipment</li></ul><h4>National Attraction:</h4><p><strong>Pan-India presence</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Students:</strong> From 25 states enrolled</li><li><strong>Age Groups:</strong> 8 to 21 years</li><li><strong>Batch Size:</strong> 200+ players in training</li><li><strong>Success Rate:</strong> 30% reach national/international level</li></ul><p>India\'s <strong>table tennis revolution</strong>! ‚≠ê</p>', 'article-6-1619454823.webp', '2021-07-25', 1, 1);
